{"title":"SRAM UDH Compatible Gravel and Road Bikes List Has Grown","link":"https://theradavist.com/sram-udh-compatible-gravel-road/","date":1721771640000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/SRAM_UDH_ROAD_GRAVEL.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/SRAM_UDH_ROAD_GRAVEL.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/SRAM_UDH_ROAD_GRAVEL.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/SRAM_UDH_ROAD_GRAVEL.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/SRAM_UDH_ROAD_GRAVEL.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>The SRAM Bike Finder list of <a href=\"https://bikefinder.sram.com/universal-derailleur-hanger-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">UDH-compatible road and gravel bikes</a> seems to have grown when nobody was looking…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-6.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>A discussion unfolded in our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/state-bicycle-co-titanium-all-road-review/\" target=\"_blank\">State Bicycle Co Ti All Road review today</a> surrounding SRAM UDH compatibility on drop bar road and gravel bikes. The conversation asked a simple question: are UDH gravel and road bikes going to be more of a thing in the future? This prompted Josh to check out SRAM’s Bike Finder “<a href=\"https://bikefinder.sram.com/universal-derailleur-hanger-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Road and Gravel</a>” tab, and it seems the list has grown exponentially since Transmission launched last year as a primarily mountain bike-centric bit of tech.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Yeti-SB135-SRAM-Transmission-Review-13.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-9.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>SRAM T-Type on a <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/27-5-yeti-sb135-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Yeti SB135</a> and the lead image from our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/sram-eagle-transmission-stealth-brake-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Transmission review</a> from last year</em></p>\n<p>This means that the SRAM UDH hanger will indeed be <em>universal</em> across all bicycle platforms, but fear not, cable-actuated loyalists. <span>There will always be compatibility with (most) cable-actuated derailleurs, even for Shimano’s direct-mount derailleurs, thanks to <a href=\"https://wheelsmfg.com/blog/sram-udh-to-shimano-direct-mount.html\" target=\"_blank\">Wheels Manufacturing</a>.</span></p>\n<p>At this moment, the list of UDH road and gravel bikes will continue to grow as smaller framebuilders, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/paragon-machine-works-sram-udh/\" target=\"_blank\">component suppliers like Paragon Machine Works</a>, and companies like Fairlight, will <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/fairlight-modular-dropouts/\" target=\"_blank\">adopt their modular dropouts</a> to keep up with demand.</p>\n<p>What do you think? Is this the future for road and gravel?</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/sram-udh-compatible-gravel-road/\">SRAM UDH Compatible Gravel and Road Bikes List Has Grown</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"5001dc99a6e5291199c4ecd537b1f9ee40d720534b8604e425a0975734f3cee3","category":"Cycling"}